AreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

AreaNssaTranslatorRole.description: Indicates an NSSA border router's ability to perform NSSA translation of type-7 LSAs into type-5 LSAs.

AreaNssaTranslatorStabilityInterval.description: The number of seconds after an elected translator determines its services are no longer required

AreaSummary.description: The variable ospfAreaSummary controls the import of summary LSAs into stub and NSSA areas. It has no effect on other areas.  If it is noAreaSummary

AuthType.description: The authentication type specified for an area.

ImportAsExtern.description: Indicates if an area is a stub area
